Here's how to use clap for argument parsing:

```rust
use clap::Parser;

#[derive(Parser, Debug)]
struct Cli {
    #[arg(short, long)]
    name: String,
}

fn main() {
    let cli = Cli::parse();
    println!("Hello, {}!", cli.name);
}
```

This creates a simple CLI that accepts a `--name` argument.
